<TITLE> Tigers trail India by 15 runs at tea </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Jan 19 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh trailed India by 15 runs after reaching tea on 228-8 on the third day of the first Test against India at the Zohur Ahmed Chowdhury Stadium in Chittagong on Tuesday. Mahmudullah and Mushfiqur Rahim led the fightback for the hosts with a 108-run stand for the seventh wicket before Mushfiq was out for 44. Mahmudullah was undefeated on 63 off 102 balls with 10 fours. Shahadat Hossain (11) was the last wicket to fall when he tried to go for a lofted drive but only succeeded in getting caught at point. Resuming on 59-3 in reply to India's first innings total of 243 all out, the home side lost three more wickets to end yet another delayed morning session due to foggy conditions, on 118 for six. Mohammad Ashraful departed for two, skipper Shakib Al Hasan (17) and Raqibul Hasan also for 17. Ashraful was all at sea early in the morning, playing Zaheer Khan away from the body, and getting squared up by Ishant Sharma. One sharp chance went unaccepted at second slip, but in the fifth over of the day Ishant created a much simpler opportunity which squared up the batsman and it took the shoulder of the bat towards Rahul Dravid at first slip. Shakib Al Hasan came out looking to counterattack and hit four boundaries in the next four overs. But the Bangladesh skipper played one too many an aggressive stroke and Virender Sehwag caught him in the gully. By that time the Tigers were 89-5. Sreesanth came back to end Raqibul Hasan's resistance, who too played inside the line of a straight delivery, and but for the openers Bangladesh had lost all other batsmen to outside e
